main event: On April 22, 1956, a civilian observed a single unidentified object in the sky over Madison, Wisconsin, for 2 minutes as it traveled westward.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 2 minutes,The object was reported to move westward,There was an attempt to capture a photograph, but no physical evidence was found,A policeman surveyed an unidentified object over Madison for 50 minutes without filing charges,The report has been classified as Unidentified due to insufficient data.
